@* Standalone "verify what you should see now" callout for tutorial pages.
   Sits at the end of a unit (after a <Steps> block, but valid anywhere) and
   is rendered as a styled box rather than a heading so the right-side
   "On this page" outline only lists actual section headings.

   Shares chrome and body typography with GitHub-style `[!KIND]` alerts via
   `markdown-alert` + `markdown-alert-checkpoint`. The label is text rather
   than an SVG icon — that is the sole difference from a Markdig-rendered
   alert. *@

<div class="markdown-alert markdown-alert-checkpoint not-prose">
    <p class="markdown-alert-title">Checkpoint</p>
    @ChildContent
</div>

@code {
    /// <summary>Body of the checkpoint callout — usually one or two paragraphs and a verification list.</summary>
    [Parameter] public RenderFragment? ChildContent { get; set; }
}
